{"questionId":"13340","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The plane <em>П</em><sub>1</sub> contains the points P(1, 6, −7) , Q(0, 1, 1) and R(2, 0, −4).</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The Cartesian equation of the plane <em>П</em><sub>2</sub> is given by <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x - 3y - z = 3\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>3</mn>\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mi>z</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>3</mn>\n</math></span>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>The Cartesian equation of the plane <em>П</em><sub>3</sub> is given by <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"ax + by + cz = 1\">\n  <mi>a</mi>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>b</mi>\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>c</mi>\n  <mi>z</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n</math></span>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Consider the case that <em>П</em><sub>3</sub> contains <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"L\">\n  <mi>L</mi>\n</math></span>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Show that <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"5a - 7c = 4\">\n  <mn>5</mn>\n  <mi>a</mi>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>7</mn>\n  <mi>c</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>4</mn>\n</math></span>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>substituting&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\left( {\\begin{array}{*{20}{c}}  {\\frac{5}{4}} \\\\   0 \\\\   { - \\frac{7}{4}}  \\end{array}} \\right)\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mtable rowspacing=\"4pt\" columnspacing=\"1em\">\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mfrac>\n                <mn>5</mn>\n                <mn>4</mn>\n              </mfrac>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mn>0</mn>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n        <mtr>\n          <mtd>\n            <mrow>\n              <mo>−</mo>\n              <mfrac>\n                <mn>7</mn>\n                <mn>4</mn>\n              </mfrac>\n            </mrow>\n          </mtd>\n        </mtr>\n      </mtable>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span> into&nbsp;<em>П</em><sub>3</sub>:&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{5a}}{4} - \\frac{{7c}}{4} = 1\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>5</mn>\n      <mi>a</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mn>4</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>7</mn>\n      <mi>c</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mn>4</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"5a -&nbsp;7c =&nbsp;4\">\n  <mn>5</mn>\n  <mi>a</mi>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>7</mn>\n  <mi>c</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>4</mn>\n</math></span> &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"13340","referenceCode":"19M.2.AHL.TZ2.H_11d.i","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Show that 5 a − 7 c = 4 .","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"d.i","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.17—Vector equations of a plane","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","AHL 3.18—Intersections of lines & planes"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}